annotationA: Vacuolar protein sorting-associated protein 33A; Required for the biogenesis of eye pigment granules. Plays a role in vesicle-mediated protein trafficking to lysosomal compartments and in membrane docking/fusion reactions of late endosomes/lysosomes; Belongs to the STXBP/unc-18/SEC1 family
annotationB: Vacuolar protein sorting 33B; Protein binding; syntaxin binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of SNARE complex assembly; endosomal transport; spindle assembly involved in mitosis; vesicle docking involved in exocytosis; imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis; vesicle-mediated transport; immune response; Belongs to the STXBP/unc-18/SEC1 family
